:: \ Ask Baba Yaga {"position":"6800,700","size":"100,100"}
I follow her into a small kitchen and take a seat at the dinning table where Baba Yaga busies herself fixing us both a plate of food and drink. 

[after 5 seconds]
"Grandmother please allow me"  \
Baba Yaga nods approvingly and takes her seat while I begin serving her food. 

[after 10 seconds]
"Thank you child, these cold winter nights do rattle these old bones so...Good to see all those rubles and riches haven't made you forget your manners. Now tell me why did you come all this way and so late tsk tsk..."

[after 15 seconds]
I kneel at her chair  \
"Please! Grandmother, my daughter she is unwell! She doesn't eat or act how she used to! Its as if she's someone else entirely! She wails whenever I leave her side and the way she speaks! You'd think she was my mother not my daughter. I've taken her to the court physician and he claims there is nothing wrong with her, but I sense it!" 

[after 20 seconds]
[[Continue -> The Calm]]



