:: \ Flower Crown {"position":"5100,1000","size":"100,100"}
I tie my horse to a nearby tree branch and begin looking for long pieces of grass to weave together. I take reeds of cowslip and primrose braiding them into a flower crown. I take off my cloak, leaving it and the crown by the river side and say

[after 10 seconds]
"Oh maiden of these waters, please guide me on my path and allow me how to cross your river unharmed."

[after 15 seconds]
The water moves in gentle ripples towards the rivers edge and a small, webbed hand moves out of the water snatching up the cloak and crown. Then the ripples move to hide in the nearby reeds. I can only see two black eyes poke out, both as shiny and deep as river stones. 

[after 25 seconds]
"Oh what a wonderful cloak and a beautiful crown! I've never seen anything like it! You may cross my river, just this once..."

[after 30 seconds]
The river spirit sinks into the water and as she does the river parts and the river bed moves upwards revealing a small path across the river to the other side

[after 35 seconds]
