:: \ The Storm {"position":"7200,700","size":"100,100"}
I fling myself at the young girl, so dirty I barely recognized her,  "Oh my darling Lalka! How can this be? How are you here right now? I left you at the palace, what is the meaning of this?"

[after 10 seconds]
"Your precious Lalka was so sad when she couldn't be with you. Oh how you discarded her after she loved you so much...*tsk tsk*. She traded her name to see you once more! And once she saw you I collected my payment— ***HER!*** She is mine by right and you can't have her!"

[after 20 seconds]
"But this can not be! I love Lalka with all my heart! I would never discard her! She hasn't left my side! She couldn't have given you her name, tell me who gave you her name!?!"

[after 25 seconds]
Baba Yaga thought to herself for a moment and then said, "Your precious blessing bestowed by your mother. The one you named Lalka"

[after 30 seconds]
I deperately searched for the peices to connect this damning puzzle, who was she talkign about? I would never discard Lalka! And who knew of her? It must've been someone close to us, but *who*? Then it dawned on me: ***my mother's blessing***

[after 40 seconds]
"Grandmother! You have been decieved! It was my Doll that traded Lalka's name, but I **never** named my mother's blessing! That Doll paid you with something that was never hers to give! Please give my Lalka back to me!"

[after 50 seconds]
Baba Yaga roared in fury, so loud the whole hut shook with her anger. She quickly ran to the window, yanked it open and yelled outside: "Bring her to me! Bring me that lying, wicked Doll!"

[after 60 seconds]
Suddenly the winds began to whip so fiercely the shudders shook and the forrest outside moaned with the force. A loud chorus of goose honks cresendoed over the howling wind and Baba Yaga began to pace furiously while Lalka and I wept holding each other too terrified to move lest we face the Witch's wrath.

[after 60 seconds]
[[The Witch's Wrath]]


